stock to be volatile, to bounce around a lot, because every time it bounces=
 around you make money. The volatility of the underlying stock is an import=
ant input to the options calculators that the banks use to figure out how m=
uch to pay for the warrant.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When you do a d=
eal like this, one thing that you worry about is a merger. The value of the=
