d thought =E2=80=9Cwe should adjust these warrants=E2=80=9D and had other r=
easons for deciding not to. On the other hand, if one bank adjusts its warr=
ants to be worth an extra $162 million, and the other three don=E2=80=99t, =
that does tend to undermine the one bank=E2=80=99s position. The other thre=
e banks saw Musk=E2=80=99s tweets too; they just let it go.</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">Speaking of =E2=80=9Cbusiness reasons,=E2=80=9D with cases=
 like this it is fun, for me at least, to imagine the discussions within th=
e bank. Like there is some banker at JPMorgan who covers Tesla, and who is =
not particularly in the weeds of the equity derivatives book. And this cove=
rage banker was just cheerfully going about her business, planning to meet =
with Tesla and pitch some mergers and financing deals, when=C2=A0some nerd =
in=C2=A0equity derivatives called and said=C2=A0=E2=80=9Chey, heads up, we=
=E2=80=99re in a dispute with Tesla about how we calculate the adjusted str=
ike price of the warrants we did in 2014.=E2=80=9D And the coverage banker =
was probably like =E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99t know what those words mean but t=
his sounds very trivial, this is a huge company with huge prospective reven=
ue, don=E2=80=99t antagonize them, just do them a favor and calculate the a=
djusted strike price the way they want.=E2=80=9D And then the derivatives b=
anker said =E2=80=9Cno you don=E2=80=99t understand it=E2=80=99s $162 milli=
on.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then the coverage banker p=
resumably =E2=80=A6=C2=A0fainted? Like, obviously people very high up at JP=
Morgan had to sign off on filing this lawsuit, and presumably the coverage =
bankers=C2=A0advocated against it, but they had absolutely no leg to stand =
on because it takes a whole lot of banking revenue to=C2=A0compete with the=
 $162 million that the equity derivatives nerds are planning to collect fro=
m Tesla. And now Tesla presumably hates JPMorgan and doesn=E2=80=99t return=
 the coverage banker=E2=80=99s phone calls, and JPMorgan has decided as a m=
atter of corporate policy to do this anyway because very few clients are wo=
rth $162 million.</p><table class=3D"liveintent-sponsored-content" width=3D=
