f4b8524a319a23cBd0b1ca45" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ta=
rget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; =
border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style=
: solid; background-color: #ccc;">it with me now</a>!</p><blockquote><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ohio=E2=80=99s attorney general is suing Meta Platfo=
rms Inc., formerly known as Facebook Inc., alleging the company misled the =
public about how it controlled its algorithm and the effects its products h=
ave on children.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The lawsuit, filed on beha=
lf of Meta investors and the Ohio Public Employees Retirement System, seeks=
 more than $100 billion in damages and demands that Meta make significant c=
hanges so as to not mislead investors again, Ohio Attorney General Dave Yos=
t said in a statement. =E2=80=A6</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The lawsui=
t alleges that between April 29 and Oct. 21, 2021, Facebook and its executi=
ves violated federal securities law by intentionally misleading the public =
about the negative impact of its products on minors in an effort to boost i=
ts stock and deceive shareholders.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=
=9CFacebook said it was looking out for our children and weeding out online=
 trolls, but in reality was creating misery and divisiveness for profit,=E2=
=80=9D Mr. Yost, a Republican, said.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16=
px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/257=
23599.270661/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cub2hpb2F0dG9ybmV5Z2VuZXJhbC5nb3YvRmlsZXMvQnJpZW=
ZpbmctUm9vbS9OZXdzLVJlbGVhc2VzL0ZhY2Vib29rLUluaXRpYWwtQ29tcGxhaW50LShGaWxlZ=
CkuYXNweA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9c1d78a7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the complaint</a>. You=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25723599.270661/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMDMvZ29s=
ZG1hbi1zYWNocy1nb2VzLXRvLXN1cHJlbWUtY291cnQtaGVkZ2UtZnVuZHMtd29uLW9uLWdhbWV=
zdG9wLWtrcG9lNndzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMTYyMV9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haW=
wmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIxMTExNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZ=
XlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBbaef1638" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> know the drill</a> by=
 now.=C2=A0Facebook said some generic things about how it was good:</p><blo=
ckquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Throughout the Class Period, the Compa=
ny repeatedly assured investors that it has =E2=80=9Cthe most robust set of=
 content policies out there=E2=80=9D and touted the aggressive steps it tak=
es to ensure the safety and security of its users by preventing misinformat=
ion and harmful content from spreading through its platforms. Facebook also=
 stated that it was committed to keeping people safe and assured investors =
that it enforces its content policies evenly across all users.=C2=A0</p></b=
lockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And investors, reassured by those st=
atements, assumed that Facebook was good and bought its stock. But in fact =
it was bad:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Thousands of recent=
ly leaked internal Facebook documents paint a remarkably different picture.=
 Those documents show that Defendants were acutely aware that the products =
and systems central to Facebook=E2=80=99s business are riddled with flaws t=
hat sow dissention, facilitate illegal activity and violent extremism, and =
cause significant harm to users, but Facebook lacks the will or ability to =
correct them. Despite this knowledge, Facebook opted to maximize its profit=
s at the expense of the safety of its users and the broader public, exposin=
g Facebook to serious reputational, legal, and financial harm.</p></blockqu=
ote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And, when the facts (that Facebook was bad=
) came out, the stock went down:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">From the date of the first article published by The Wall Street Journal o=
n September 13, 2021 to The Wall Street Journal article published on Octobe=
r 21, 2021 that raised concerns about the accuracy and reliability of the C=
ompany=E2=80=99s user metrics, Facebook=E2=80=99s stock price declined by $=
54.08 per share, or over 14%, representing a decline of more than $150 bill=
ion in Facebook=E2=80=99s total market capitalization.</p></blockquote><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you were the attorney general of Ohio and you w=
ere interested in =E2=80=9Clooking out for our children,=E2=80=9D it is not=
=C2=A0<em>obvious=C2=A0</em>that the right mechanism for that would be to t=
ry to recover billions of dollars of damages for=C2=A0<em>Meta shareholders=
</em>? Those shareholders are the ones who enjoyed the profits that Faceboo=
k was allegedly maximizing =E2=80=9Cat the expense of the safety of its use=
rs and the broader public.=E2=80=9D Arguably if you are a state attorney ge=
neral you should be protecting the broader public=C2=A0<em>from=C2=A0</em>M=
eta and its owners, not trying to recover more money for Meta=E2=80=99s own=
ers. But this ship has sailed, nobody thinks it=E2=80=99s weird, everything=
 is securities fraud.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And, sure, fair. Imag=
ine the attorney general of Ohio trying to sue Meta on behalf of children w=
ho were negatively impacted by using Facebook and Instagram. He=E2=80=99d h=
ave to find the children in Ohio who used Facebook and Instagram, and figur=
e out how sad Facebook and Instagram made them. It would be hard to turn th=
at into a damages claim, especially one with a big dollar number; how much =
is a child=E2=80=99s sadness worth in dollars? He could seek an injunction =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0not =E2=80=9Cpay us money=E2=80=9D but rather =E2=80=9Cchang=
e your policies to be nicer to children=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94=C2=A0but that wo=
uld require him to figure out what the right policies are, which is not eas=
y! But if bad documents come out of Facebook and the stock goes down by $15=
0 billion, then that=E2=80=99s a big lawsuit with clear victims (the shareh=
olders) and clear damages ($150 billion). And if Facebook wants to avoid la=
wsuits like that, well, it can figure out what policies to write so that it=
s stock doesn=E2=80=99t drop again.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25723599.270661/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cudGhlZGlmZi5jby9wL2FkdmVydGlzaW5nLWFuZC1zdHJhdGVnaWMtY29uc3VsdGluZw/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB964b0f7c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Byrne Hobart writes</a> that =E2=
=80=9Ceverything is securities fraud=E2=80=9D is =E2=80=9Cpartly a result o=
f how efficiently markets aggregate and share information: it's hard to dir=
ectly measure the effect of corporate malfeasance on sales or employee rete=
ntion, especially over long periods. But stock prices react fast, and they =
represent a guess about the long term. So if you want to know=C2=A0<em>exac=
tly</em>=C2=A0how bad some piece of news was, the only way to rephrase that=
=C2=A0is =E2=80=98how bad was it=C2=A0<em>for shareholders</em>?=E2=80=99=
=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I do not disagree with this but <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25723599.270661/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMTAtMDQvZmFjZW=
